<http://www.isid.org>
See Also
BSE - Czech Republic 20010609.1127
Date: 16 June 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE <http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm>

BOVINE SPONGIFORM ENCEPHALOPATHY IN THE CZECH REPUBLIC
-------------------------------------------------------
(Disease never previously reported)
Emergency report
Information received on 8 and 14 Jun 2001 from Dr Josef Holejsovsky, Chief
Veterinary Officer, State Veterinary Administration, Prague:
Final date of report: 13 Jun 2001
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 5 Jun 2001
Outbreaks:
Location: Jihlava district
No. of outbreaks: 1
Description of affected population: the affected animal was a 68-month-old
cow from a holding of breeding cows. Before being slaughtered on 4 Jun 2001
it had not moved from the farm where it was born on 28 Sep 1995
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species/ susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
bov/ 138/ 1/ 0/ 138/ 0
Diagnosis: the animal was tested within the framework of the compulsory
testing for BSE of all bovine animals over 30 months of age subject to
slaughter.
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: State Veterinary Institute,
Jihlava. Confirmation at the European reference laboratory in TÃ¼bingen,
Germany.
B. Diagnostic tests used: western blot, immunohistochemistry.
Source of agent / origin of infection: not yet known
Investigations are in progress.
Control measures:
1. In the herd of origin:
- Eradication by the methods "cohort cull" and "offspring cull". All culled
animals will be tested. Animals found to be positive will be destroyed by
incineration. In the case of negative test results, the animals will be
destroyed by burying.
- All dead and slaughtered animals not from the cohort or the offspring
will be compulsorily tested by western blot.
- Movement restrictions, with the exception of movement to slaughterhouse
with veterinary certificate.
2. In slaughterhouses:
- All bovine animals over 30 months of age subject to slaughter have been
compulsorily tested for BSE since 12 Jun 2001.
- Ban on production of mechanically recovered meat from bones of bovine
animals since 18 Jun 2001.
- Removal of specified risk materials (SRM) from the food chain applied
since 1 Jan 2000. Separate processing of SRM from slaughterhouses and
rendering plants and transport to one designated rendering plant since 18
Jun 2001.
